---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer | Autism Signals"
  description="Important boundaries and disclaimer language for the Autism Signals self-check experience."
>
  <main class="page-shell legal-shell">
    <section class="legal-page">
      <div class="legal-card">
        <a class="legal-back" href="/">Back to Autism Signals</a>

        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--soft">Disclaimer</p>
        <h1>Clear boundaries, stated plainly.</h1>
        <p class="legal-intro">
          Autism Signals is an informational self-check for reflection only. It is intentionally
          careful about what it can and cannot tell someone.
        </p>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Not a diagnosis or validated screening tool</h2>
          <p>
            Autism Signals is not clinically validated, not an official screen, and not a
            substitute for professional diagnosis. A result on this site does not confirm or rule
            out autism.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Not medical or mental health advice</h2>
          <p>
            The content on this site is provided for general informational and self-reflection
            purposes only. It should not be treated as medical advice, mental health advice, or a
            recommendation about treatment, medication, or care.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Short tools have limits</h2>
          <p>
            A brief questionnaire cannot capture every reason someone may relate to autistic
            traits. Stress, burnout, trauma, anxiety, ADHD, sensory sensitivity, or other
            experiences can overlap with some of the themes discussed here.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Use the result as one data point</h2>
          <p>
            If the reflection resonates, treat it as a starting point for careful reading,
            journaling, conversation, and self-understanding rather than a verdict.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Urgent support</h2>
          <p>
            Autism Signals is not an emergency service. If you are in immediate danger or need
            urgent mental health support in the United States, call or text <strong>988</strong>
            or contact local emergency services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>External resources</h2>
          <p>
            Links to third-party resources are offered for convenience and further reading. They
            do not guarantee accuracy for every person or situation, and inclusion does not
            create a professional relationship or endorsement.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
